  "phase26_ingest_note": "The CISI Vol 3 Part 3 PDF text extract gives us the site-prefix structure but not sign-by-sign content (which lives in image plates not parseable from text). To populate indus_signs[] for the 10 length-only Mesopotamia-found seals, we need either: (a) high-resolution plate scans + manual sign-ID assignment, (b) targeted requests to Parpola/Frenez/Laursen for digital sign-ID lists, or (c) the CISI Vol 3 Part 3 supplementary digital catalogue from the Finnish Academy of Science. Phase-26 acquires the prefix-to-site mapping (above), enabling provenience-aware filtering, but does NOT populate the seal-level sign sequences themselves.",
  "shu_ilishu_candidate_filter_criteria": "For each Indus inscription of length 3-7, check if its site prefix is in the contact-zone set (Shd, Sap, Sh, Mgk, etc., or Mesopotamia/Dilmun/Failaka external prefix). The 138 Phase-25e candidate inscriptions can be reduced to those with contact-zone provenience for a tighter Shu-ilishu candidate list."
